headline.main: HESS SOUGHT PACT, NAZI SOURCE AVERS; German Paper in Sweden Says Hitler Sent Aide to Britain With Anti-Soviet Plan

lead_paragraph: STOCKHOLM, Sweden, Oct. 2 -- That Adolf Hitler sent Rudolf Hess to Britain as his personal envoy, to propose to the British a tie-up with the Tripartite Alliance against Soviet Russia, has been admitted for the first time by a Nazi source.
abstract: Stockholm Dagsposten reveals Hitler sent R Hess to Brit to propose tie-up with Tripartite Pact signers against USSR; plan discussed
